payload: As some of you might already know, I resigned today. I feel fortunate and blessed to have had this experience here at Enron. Not only have I learned a tremendous amount, but I also have met some very talented and unique people. I am not 100% sure what I will do at this point, but I will probably be heading up to NYC in January. I feel sad to end this chapter, yet excited as I begin a new one in my life. As always, it has been a pleasure working with you! Keep in touch. I will be interested to see what happens. Carole C. payload: Paul, Could you set aside some time today to talk to me about the recent Kennedy Oil deal in addition to 2 other deals. These other deals were discovered in our bid week preparations, and are causing our desk some pretty big negative Prior Month Adjustments. So, we need to get these resolved. The first one is the Williams / wic deal. The deal #'s for that are 121890,854562, & 1068893. The reason for the split of this deal is b/c our books changed names. The second deal in question which needs to be resolved a.s.a.p. is a Red Rock Energy LLC deal #133661. This deal is being booked to Denver in Sitara, but in Tagg the risk is going to Keith Holst and Mike Grigsby. Please look over these deals and let me know when a good time to talk will be. Thank you! Carole C, Frank Enron Net Works 713.345.3960 work 713.446.9307 cell

payload: Darron, I met this man's wife, Nadia Rodriquez, in orientation. Here is what she said about her husband's work experience. "My husband just finished his MBA and his company's moving to Atlanta. He has been offered two positions there but we would rather stay here. His background has been in the securities industry, most recently in compliance where he ensures that brokers follow NASD and SEC regulations in all aspects (e.g. trading, marketing, etc.). Prior to the compliance role, he was a broker with PaineWebber. Also, he has extensive computer skills and is used to dealing with all levels of personnel." She should be sending me his resume soon. Carole

payload: Paul, Could you set aside some time today to talk to me about the recent Kennedy Oil deal in addition to 2 other deals. The first one is the Williams / wic deal. The deal #'s for that are 121890,854562, & 1068893. The reason for the split of this deal is b/c our books changed names. The second deal in question which needs to be resolved a.s.a.p. is a Red Rock Energy LLC deal #133661. This deal is being booked to Denver in Sitara, but in Tagg the risk is going to Keith Holst and Mike Grigsby. Please look over these deals and let me know when a good time to talk will be. Thank you!
